iod. Chapters explore food, identity, gender, and the role of writing in Thúy’s life and work. Thúy herself contributes an unpublished poem and an extended interview that focus on her ongoing struggle to find, and write, beauty amidst war, migration, poverty, and loss. Touching Beauty maps the themes that have, to date, animated a literary career of global relevance and enduring value and encourages a deeper appreciation of Thúy’s writing.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Women Authors.2bisacsh  a20th century.  a21st century.  aCanada.  aFrench.  aKim-Van-Kieu.  aMontreal.  aParis.  aQuebec.  aVietnam.  aautism.  aboat.  achildren.  acon gai.  acooking.  aepistolary.  aethnicity.  aexile.  afamily.  afoodways.  agender.  ahybrid.  aidentity.  aimmigrant.  aintercultural.  ainternational.  aliterature.  amarriage.  amedia.  ametis.  amigrant.  amixed.  amothering.  amultilingual.  anovel.  apeople.  apoetry.  arefugee.  arestaurant.  asecrets.  asilence.  astorytelling.  atransnational.  atrauma.  awar.1 aHu’o’ng, Nguyễn Giáng, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKistnareddy, Ashwiny O., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReid, Amy B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRogers, Juliette M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSantoro, Miléna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSantoro, Miléna, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aThúy, Kim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYeager, Jack A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYeager, Jack A., eeditor.4edt4http